# Dosu Logi Architecture (mandatory)

## Backend – Hexagonal
- Structure per domain: `internal/{domain}/domain|application|adapter/http|adapter/postgres`
- `domain/`: entities + port interfaces only. No gin, no sql, no json tags on entities if avoidable (use DTOs in adapter/http).
- `application/`: use cases, business rules. Depends only on domain ports.
- `adapter/http/`: handlers, request/response DTOs, gin bindings.
- `adapter/postgres/`: repository implementations.
- NEVER import adapter from domain or application.
- Max ~200 lines per file; split by use case not by layer dump.
- API list response: `{ "data": [], "meta": { "page", "limit", "total" } }`.
- API error: `{ "error": { "code": "...", "message": "..." } }`.

## Frontend – FSD
- Layers (import only downward): `app → pages → widgets → features → entities → shared`
- `pages/`: compose widgets/features only; NO fetch logic, NO form state.
- `features/`: user actions (modal forms, filters); may use entities API.
- `entities/`: types + api functions per entity.
- `shared/ui/`: dumb components (Modal, Table, Pagination, Button).
- Modals: always overlay via portal; never inline forms in list pages.
- Lists: always paginated server-side (`page`, `limit`); never load all records.
- One component file = one responsibility; extract hooks to `features/*/model/` or `entities/*/model/`.

## Forbidden
- Logic + UI mixed in page components.
- Handler calling SQL directly.
- New dependencies without clear need.
- Duplicating API client code outside `shared/api`.
